name: Wave 2B — checkable adjective definition
description: ```
A `Definition:` line in the vocabulary defines a checkable adjective. A
subject-position use (`if the page is stale`) lowers to a call of the
generated `meridianDef_<Kind>_<adj>` predicate, whose body emits the
`has no` emptiness check.
```
tags: inform7, wave2, codegen

vocab_inline doc: ```
=== vocabulary ===
A page is a kind of thing.
A page has a summary, which is text.
Definition: a page is stale if it has no summary.
```

source_inline: ```
---
name: review
parameters: page
vocabulary: doc.merconfig
---

To review a page:
  if the page is stale,
    complete with reason "needs work".
```

expect_compile: pass
expect_no_unresolved:
expect_workflow_count: 1
expect_workflow_named: ReviewPage
expect_swift_contains: private func meridianDef_Page_stale(
expect_swift_contains: MeridianComparison.isEmpty(
expect_swift_contains: meridianDef_Page_stale(state.get("page")
